						            <note>By contrast with Vogel, who took <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">cetiyaghara</foreign> as a
							nominative singular, we follow here the suggestion
							of <bibl>
								                <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Sircar1942"/>:
									<citedRange>227 n. 2</citedRange>
							              </bibl>; <bibl>
								                <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Sircar1965"/>:
									<citedRange>236 n. 3</citedRange>
